    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stone monuments with either incised text and/or images. The inscriptions found on bei in northern China heavily influenced the epigraphic school of calligraphy and painting during the Qing dynasty (1644-1911) and early Republican era (1912-1949).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
